Package org.apache.drill.exec.vector

Class RepeatedDecimal28DenseVector

java.lang.Object
org.apache.drill.exec.vector.BaseValueVector
org.apache.drill.exec.vector.complex.BaseRepeatedValueVector
org.apache.drill.exec.vector.RepeatedDecimal28DenseVector
All Implemented Interfaces:
Closeable, AutoCloseable, Iterable<ValueVector>, ContainerVectorLike, RepeatedFixedWidthVectorLike, RepeatedValueVector, ValueVector
public final class RepeatedDecimal28DenseVector extends BaseRepeatedValueVector implements RepeatedFixedWidthVectorLike
RepeatedDecimal28Dense implements a vector with multiple values per row (e.g. JSON array or repeated protobuf field). The implementation uses an additional value vectors to convert the index offset to the underlying element offset. The count of values comes from subtracting two successive offsets. NB: this class is automatically generated from RepeatedValueVectors.java and ValueVectorTypes.tdd using FreeMarker.
